ELLEN TERRY WITH MARION TERRY HER SISTER

relatedItem.note: in 1911, seated in the old school desk (a little wooden affair with wooden seat and with two flap-lids for sloping writing places) made for her children Edith and Edward. A Note on the back of the picture in Ellen Terry's handwriting reads: "For my book but it never appeared in her book. The print is excessively rare, not reproduced befor e and by no means a clear print; but very pretty of both sisters. Plate 18
